<TITLE> Sylhet's Kamran to be paroled Monday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sylhet, Aug 17 (bdnews24.com)  Detained Sylhet city mayor-elect Badaruddin Ahmed Kamran will be freed on parole Monday to pay his last respects to his mother, a senior prisons official said Sunday. Kamran's mother Nurennesa Khanam Lalon, 80, died in Square Hospital Sunday afternoon from old-age complications. "Kamran is being transferred to Sylhet prison from Comilla. He will be released on parole Monday morning," said inspector general of prisons, Brig Gen Zakir Hasan. bdnews24.com Sylhet correspondent reported that Nurennesa Khanam was very active in the most recent and previous election campaigns for her son. Kamran was elected Sylhet mayor on Aug 4 by a huge margin. bdnews2
